The paper focuses on analyzing the structural properties and impact of social network properties on user activities in an online content voting network, specifically Digg. This involves studying user behavior, content promotion, and information filtering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
